From: Quinn Tran <quinn.tran@cavium.com>
Date: Tue, 11 Sep 2018 10:18:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] scsi: qla2xxx: Fix port speed display on chip reset
References: bsc#1108870
Git-commit: 5d74c87a20adcc77b19753c315ad9c320b2288be
Patch-mainline: v4.20-rc1

Clear port speed value on chip reset.

Signed-off-by: Quinn Tran <quinn.tran@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Himanshu Madhani <himanshu.madhani@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_init.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_init.c b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_init.c
index 096743331ec4..4d04603dd4ae 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_init.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/qla2xxx/qla_init.c
@@ -6560,6 +6560,7 @@ qla2x00_abort_isp_cleanup(scsi_qla_host_t *vha)
 	if (!(IS_P3P_TYPE(ha)))
 		ha->isp_ops->reset_chip(vha);
 
+	ha->link_data_rate = PORT_SPEED_UNKNOWN;
 	SAVE_TOPO(ha);
 	ha->flags.rida_fmt2 = 0;
 	ha->flags.n2n_ae = 0;
